to pay you something.

15:40.570 --> 15:43.130
No, you don't. No.
Next time. I'm Simone.

15:43.170 --> 15:44.262
Oh, um, Alicia.

15:44.310 --> 15:47.006
There aren't many
people around here.
Yes, I know.

15:47.040 --> 15:49.679
It's so strange that they built
this big hotel up here.

15:49.710 --> 15:52.008
So, are you here
for vacation or something?

15:52.050 --> 15:54.018
Oh, no. Work. You?
Uh.

15:54.050 --> 15:55.415
Oh, my husband's here for work.

15:56.720 --> 16:00.281
You are probably the lavwer
that he's here to meet.

16:00.320 --> 16:01.981
Are you Mrs. Canning?

16:02.020 --> 16:03.021
Yes. Are you
Mrs. Florrick?

16:03.060 --> 16:04.584
Yes.
My husband

16:04.630 --> 16:06.154
speaks so highly of you.

16:06.190 --> 16:08.124
He does?
Yes.

16:08.160 --> 16:09.650
He does.
He thinks you're fantastic.

16:13.200 --> 16:14.997
(laughs)
I'm joking.

16:15.040 --> 16:15.995
But we should have breakfast
sometime.

16:16.040 --> 16:19.032
You know, if we're going
to be here for a while.

16:19.070 --> 16:21.630
Are we going to be here
for a while?

16:21.680 --> 16:23.773
I don't know.
You tell me.

16:23.810 --> 16:26.199
(laughs)
(laughs)

16:26.250 --> 16:27.774
Well, it was really
nice to meet you.

16:27.820 --> 16:29.378
So, I'll call you for breakfast?

16:29.420 --> 16:31.240
Good. Yeah.
Okay.

16:33.260 --> 16:35.216
Simone?

16:35.260 --> 16:36.318
Yes?

16:36.360 --> 16:40.592
I was so sorry to hear
about your husband's friend.

16:40.630 --> 16:43.064
The one who's dying?

16:43.100 --> 16:44.362
Who's that?

16:46.430 --> 16:48.694
Oh, never mind.
It was my mistake.

16:48.740 --> 16:51.061
It was lovely
to meet you, Simone.

16:51.110 --> 16:53.271
You, as well, Alicia.

16:56.180 --> 16:58.375
Good job, Kalinda.
He's sure?

16:58.410 --> 17:01.140
Yeah. Look,
as far as I can tell,

17:01.180 --> 17:03.819
the Aedus...
Eedus...? Aed...?

17:03.850 --> 17:06.080
Aedes albopictus.

17:06.120 --> 17:07.678
The...

17:07.720 --> 17:10.655
This kind of mosquito breed
doesn't transmit West Nile,

17:10.690 --> 17:13.090
so it couldn't have come
from the koi pond.

17:13.130 --> 17:16.827
That virus is transmitted
by the ae-aed...

17:16.860 --> 17:19.567
The other one?
Aedes aegypti.

17:19.600 --> 17:21.795
Aedes aegypti.

17:21.840 --> 17:24.229
By a different
type of mosquito.

17:24.270 --> 17:25.407
Excellent. Very good.

17:25.440 --> 17:27.203
Just get him on the record.

17:27.240 --> 17:28.798
Ah, that'll be fun.

17:31.150 --> 17:32.799
We'll call you
back, Kalinda.

17:33.850 --> 17:36.148
What's going on
out there?

17:37.450 --> 17:39.816
He's getting Cary in line
to testify against us.

17:39.850 --> 17:42.455
I just want to make sure
we're on the same page.

17:44.560 --> 17:46.551
Good. Thank you, Cary.

17:50.530 --> 17:52.623
Cary?

17:52.670 --> 17:54.467
Yes?

17:54.500 --> 17:56.263
What was Clarke discussing
with you?

17:56.300 --> 17:57.608
Uh, nothing.
He just wanted to know

17:57.640 --> 17:59.164
about the clients
who left last week.

17:59.210 --> 18:00.234
And what did you say?

18:00.280 --> 18:01.508
I said nothing.

18:01.540 --> 18:03.405
I just listened.
We're just a little

18:03.450 --> 18:06.374
worried he's trying to line
up a case against us, Cary.

18:06.410 --> 18:08.742
And that he
might use you.

18:08.780 --> 18:10.213
Do you think
that's a possibility?

18:10.250 --> 18:12.389
He didn't say anything
about that.

18:15.190 --> 18:17.181
Can we, um, talk to you, Cary,

18:17.230 --> 18:20.119
about possibly
testifying for us?

18:20.160 --> 18:21.297
(crows cawing)

18:21.330 --> 18:24.766
2:30. And here we are again.

18:24.800 --> 18:27.394
Why don't you go for a walk?
I'll get you when he comes.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.431
(laughs)

18:31.440 --> 18:33.579
How's your friend who's dying?

18:33.610 --> 18:35.407
Have you heard any more
from him?

18:35.440 --> 18:37.647
No. Why?

18:37.680 --> 18:40.877
Maybe you should call him.

18:40.920 --> 18:43.718
Maybe he's dead.

18:44.750 --> 18:46.638
Excuse me?

18:46.690 --> 18:48.658
Oh, I'm sorry.

18:48.690 --> 18:50.385
Am I being insensitive?

18:50.430 --> 18:52.489
How's the eulogy coming? I mean,

18:52.530 --> 18:54.589
maybe you could ask Simone
to help you on that.

18:54.630 --> 18:56.848
You met my wife.

18:56.900 --> 18:58.424
Yes, I did.

18:58.470 --> 19:00.335
She's wonderful.

19:00.370 --> 19:03.407
Yes, she's...
my better half.

19:03.440 --> 19:04.668
She's your only half.

19:04.710 --> 19:06.302
Funny, she'd never

19:06.340 --> 19:08.535
heard of Ian Keyes,
your roommate.

19:08.580 --> 19:10.741
Yeah, well...

19:10.780 --> 19:12.748
I don't share everything
with her.

19:12.780 --> 19:14.372
Your lies, for example.

19:14.420 --> 19:15.478
You don't share your lies?

19:15.520 --> 19:17.340
No.

19:17.390 --> 19:19.187
Those I save for you.

19:19.220 --> 19:20.357
(laughs)

19:20.390 --> 19:22.210
What was even the point

19:22.260 --> 19:24.751
of lying
about a dying friend?

19:24.790 --> 19:26.621
I don't know. _
It was a way of connecting.

19:26.660 --> 19:28.355
Didn't you feel
we were connected?

19:28.400 --> 19:32.291
How does a bastard like you end
up with such a wonderful wife?

19:32.330 --> 19:33.763
Women like bastards.

19:33.800 --> 19:35.438
Didn't you notice that?
It's like a challenge.

19:35.470 --> 19:36.630
Beauty and the Beast.

19:36.670 --> 19:39.707
It fits in with all the fairy
tales you grew up consuming.

19:39.740 --> 19:40.877
(laughing):
Oh, my God.

19:40.910 --> 19:42.275
(phone ringing)
Oh, there's Godot.

19:43.310 --> 19:45.301
Hello.

19:47.380 --> 19:48.847
All right. Really?

19:48.880 --> 19:52.316
Let the record show
that Mr. Ingersol has refused

19:52.350 --> 19:55.808
to attend a court-mandated
deposition for the fourth time.

19:55.860 --> 19:56.986
He was literally

19:57.020 --> 19:59.329
a minute away
when he had another call.
Oh, really?

19:59.360 --> 20:00.395
Just a minute away? Wow.

20:00.430 --> 20:02.898
He says he can reschedule
for tomorrow at 10:00.

20:02.930 --> 20:05.694
Okay, sure.
Um, it'll just...

20:05.730 --> 20:08.858
It'll give you some time
to read this.

20:08.900 --> 20:12.802
It's saying that the CDC
is updating their report again.

20:12.840 --> 20:13.977
The mosquito carrying

20:14.010 --> 20:17.002
the West Nile virus could not
have come from the koi pond.

20:17.040 --> 20:18.302
That's the wrong kind
of mosquito.

20:18.350 --> 20:21.444
The right kind of mosquito
could only

20:21.480 --> 20:23.243
have_ come
from the swnmmlng pools.

20:23.290 --> 20:27.317
So, nice try, Mr. Canning,
but you lost.

20:27.360 --> 20:29.487
And every day
that this deposition is delayed,

20:29.520 --> 20:31.579
the judge is getting angrier,
so...

20:31.630 --> 20:32.927
(clicks tongue)

20:32.960 --> 20:34.393
...might want
to rethink your strategy.

20:36.800 --> 20:39.428
(dialing touch tones)

20:39.470 --> 20:42.030
Yeah, it's me.

20:42.070 --> 20:44.436
Yeah, I need you
to look into something.

20:46.040 --> 20:47.837
So, Kaley, hi.

20:47.880 --> 20:48.699
Hi.

20:48.740 --> 20:49.775
I just want to ask you
a few questions,

20:49.810 --> 20:52.677
and I know they might seem odd
to you, but please

20:52.710 --> 20:54.519
bear with me.
Have you ever

20:54.550 --> 20:56.745
heard of Aedes aegypti?

20:56.780 --> 20:58.589
No.

20:58.620 --> 21:00.554
Well, I can understand why.

21:00.590 --> 21:04.026
That's a very long word
for a very small mosquito.

21:04.060 --> 21:06.654
You don't have to patronize her.
She's not eight years old.

21:06.690 --> 21:08.920
Thank you, Mr. Agos.

21:08.960 --> 21:09.892
This is

21:09.930 --> 21:11.921
an Aedes aegypti, Kaley.

21:11.970 --> 21:13.028
This is the breed of mosquito

21:13.070 --> 21:15.061
that carries the
West Nile virus.

21:15.100 --> 21:17.068
We didn't know_that until
your attorneys pomted It out,

21:17.100 --> 21:18.431
so thank you, Mr. Gardner,

21:18.470 --> 21:19.903
Mr. Agos.
What do you have?

21:19.940 --> 21:21.578
Now here are

21:21.610 --> 21:24.670
diagrams of the five
abandoned swimming pools

21:24.710 --> 21:26.041
that bred
the moquItoes.

21:26.080 --> 21:28.014
WILL:
Seems you've dropped
the "supposedly."

21:28.050 --> 21:29.813
Are we in agreement, the
pools bred these mosquitoes?

21:29.850 --> 21:31.681
Yes, we are.
Hallelujah.

21:31.720 --> 21:34.450
Now, here are five diagrams
of the five

21:34.490 --> 21:37.482
backyards, and
do you see here?

21:37.530 --> 21:39.919
Here are the distances
between the pools

21:39.960 --> 21:40.995
and the perimeter fences.

21:41.030 --> 21:42.827
30 yards, 40 yards.

21:42.860 --> 21:43.690
And so on.
Do you see?

21:43.730 --> 21:44.822
Yes.

21:44.870 --> 21:46.360
The thing about Aedes aegypti:

21:46.400 --> 21:47.537
they are peridomestic

21:47.570 --> 21:49.367
mosquitoes.

21:49.400 --> 21:50.958
That means they exhibit
short flight ranges

21:51.010 --> 21:52.830
of less than 50 feet.

21:52.870 --> 21:55.009
That means there is no way
they could have flown beyond

21:55.040 --> 21:56.439
their respective yards.

21:56.480 --> 21:57.071
Are you testifying here, Martha?

21:57.110 --> 21:58.771
All preamble.

21:58.810 --> 22:00.072
Here's my question.

22:00.110 --> 22:02.670
Kaley, did you climb the fence

22:02.720 --> 22:04.517
into one of these
abandoned yards?

22:08.590 --> 22:09.989
Sorry to ask you
again, Kaley,

22:10.020 --> 22:11.783
but you must
tell the truth here.

22:11.830 --> 22:13.889
Did you climb the fence
into one or more

22:13.930 --> 22:16.091
of the yards of these
abandoned houses?

22:16.130 --> 22:17.563
(sniffles)

22:17.600 --> 22:19.522
One.

22:19.570 --> 22:20.992
With my friends.

22:21.040 --> 22:23.702
Then, I'm sorry,
but the plaintiff

22:23.740 --> 22:25.105
trespassed onto
our property,

22:25.140 --> 22:28.769
and we cannot be held liable
for that trespass.

22:28.810 --> 22:30.471
This suit is over.

22:40.690 --> 22:43.420
My name is Serafina Norvey,
and before we get started,

22:43.460 --> 22:45.553
I'd like to set the ground rules
for this mediation.

22:45.590 --> 22:49.094
Granted, we're in your offices,
and outside those doors,

22:49.130 --> 22:52.520
you may all be bosses,
but in here, I am the empress.

22:52.570 --> 22:54.936
Now, I understand,

22:54.970 --> 22:55.994
as the court-appointed trustee,

22:56.040 --> 22:56.995
you'd like to have

22:57.040 --> 22:59.099
the two principals removed
as managing partners?

22:59.140 --> 22:59.936
CLARKE:
Yes.

22:59.970 --> 23:01.835
