a great deal of money

23:32.140 --> 23:33.437
in a short amount of time.

23:33.480 --> 23:34.629
How much?

23:34.680 --> 23:35.635
Excuse me?

23:35.680 --> 23:36.669
How much money?

23:36.710 --> 23:37.677
$20 million.

23:37.710 --> 23:38.972
Which is 40
million short

23:39.010 --> 23:39.977
of what they need.

23:40.010 --> 23:41.170
WILL:
And we are very close

23:41.220 --> 23:42.517
to finalizing
a $13 million settlement

23:42.550 --> 23:44.188
with Atlantic
Commerce Bank.

23:44.220 --> 23:45.118
They are not "very close."

23:45.150 --> 23:46.185
They are in deposition.

23:46.220 --> 23:48.085
Which is how it works,
Mr. Hayden.

23:48.120 --> 23:49.109
You negotiate
in depositions.

23:49.160 --> 23:51.025
You try to stay out of court.

23:51.060 --> 23:53.028
Ma'am, if we had a trustee
who understood the law...

23:53.060 --> 23:55.551
Excuse me.
I know as much as anyone...!

23:55.600 --> 23:57.192
All right,
all right.

23:57.230 --> 23:58.697
This is not marriage court.

23:58.730 --> 24:01.062
I'm not here to make you
like each other.

24:01.100 --> 24:02.795
But, Ms. Lockhart,

24:02.840 --> 24:04.068
Mr. Gardner,
I think you're losing sight

24:04.110 --> 24:05.463
of the big picture here.

24:05.510 --> 24:07.728
This isn't about you.

24:07.780 --> 24:08.906
This is about
your creditors.

24:08.940 --> 24:10.601
Yes, Your Honor.
"Ma'am."

24:10.650 --> 24:12.003
I'm not a judge.

24:12.050 --> 24:14.974
Excuse me, ma'am.

24:15.020 --> 24:17.944
Our creditors are voting
with their pocketbook

24:17.990 --> 24:19.218
by buying up our debt.

24:19.250 --> 24:21.081
They are?
WILL:
Yes.

24:21.120 --> 24:21.950
We recently got in touch

24:21.990 --> 24:23.958
with our creditors
about this mediation,

24:23.990 --> 24:26.857
and they informed us that they
no longer are our creditors.

24:26.890 --> 24:29.723
A consortium of financiers
called Encinal Equity

24:29.760 --> 24:31.068
has purchased their debt.

24:31.100 --> 24:33.091
And people don't buy bad debt.

24:33.130 --> 24:34.597
Yes, but by
that logic,

24:34.640 --> 24:37.666
your creditors are fleeing
your debt by selling it.

24:37.710 --> 24:39.200
People don't sell good debt.

24:39.240 --> 24:41.003
DIANE:
Ma'am, all we ask is

24:41.040 --> 24:43.508
for enough time
to present our arguments.

24:43.550 --> 24:44.847
This mediation has come

24:44.880 --> 24:45.949
as quite a surprise to us.

24:45.980 --> 24:47.516
How long will you need?

24:47.550 --> 24:48.676
We should be prepared
to present

24:48.720 --> 24:49.846
witnesses and evidence
by next week.

24:49.880 --> 24:52.041
Tomorrow.

24:52.090 --> 24:53.910
CARY: Let's talk about
the swimming pool

24:53.960 --> 24:55.780
at 233 Graham Court.

24:55.820 --> 24:57.117
This one here.

24:57.160 --> 24:59.025
This pool had several
water features, correct?

24:59.060 --> 25:00.186
I'm not sure
what you mean.

25:00.230 --> 25:01.254
In addition to having

25:01.300 --> 25:02.449
a deep end and a shallow end,

25:02.500 --> 25:05.219
there was also a diving board,
a waterfall, and a grotto?

25:05.270 --> 25:06.567
Okay.

25:06.600 --> 25:07.794
I agree.

25:07.840 --> 25:10.229
Was the grotto boarded up
after the bank took possession?

25:10.270 --> 25:12.033
No.

25:14.040 --> 25:15.974
Did you receive reports
from neighbors

25:16.010 --> 25:18.899
that the waterfall feature
was being used by skateboarders?

25:18.950 --> 25:20.178
Where's this going,
gentlemen?

25:20.210 --> 25:22.019
Mr. Millam, would you admit

25:22.050 --> 25:23.688
the pool was
an attractive nuisance?

25:23.720 --> 25:24.789
Objection.

25:24.820 --> 25:25.980
That does not apply here.

25:26.020 --> 25:28.159
Kaley climbed a fence
to reach the pool.

25:28.190 --> 25:30.988
Which makes it a textbook case
of attractive nuisance.

25:31.030 --> 25:33.021
It's the responsibility
of the homeowner--

25:33.060 --> 25:34.857
mmswm,
Atlantic Commerce Bank--

25:34.900 --> 25:35.958
to secure the swimming pool

25:36.000 --> 25:38.025
and make sure it did not
become a danger to children.

25:38.070 --> 25:40.129
Once again, there was a fence,
and your client is not a child.

25:40.170 --> 25:42.229
WILL: Kaley Spence was
12 years old at the time.

25:42.270 --> 25:44.329
A very young, sheltered 12.

25:44.370 --> 25:46.304
So you were sheltered?
Is that it, Kaley?

25:46.340 --> 25:49.571
You want to question
our client, depose her.

25:53.180 --> 25:55.148
Oh, you sure are well-dressed.

25:55.180 --> 25:58.149
Thanks.

25:58.190 --> 26:00.658
And you are in my office.

26:00.690 --> 26:01.315
FRANK: Oh, I see
you two have met.

26:01.360 --> 26:05.683
Eli Gold, Jordan Karahalios.

26:05.730 --> 26:07.595
Oh!

26:07.630 --> 26:08.426
The boy wonder.

26:08.460 --> 26:10.621
(chuckles):
God, I hate that name.

26:10.670 --> 26:12.626
The ever-quotable Rahm Emanuel.

26:12.670 --> 26:14.069
Never gonna
live that down.

26:14.100 --> 26:15.692
We were headed out to see Peter.

26:15.740 --> 26:17.264
I figured you two
should meet first.

26:17.300 --> 26:20.201
Because...?

26:20.240 --> 26:22.208
FRANK: That thing
we discussed before,

26:22.240 --> 26:24.208
about how you
needed a second.

26:24.250 --> 26:25.603
I like Peter.

26:25.650 --> 26:28.118
He's not one of those
processed sales jobs.

26:28.150 --> 26:29.071
He's got grit.

26:29.120 --> 26:31.145
Jordan wants to offer
you guys some time.

26:31.190 --> 26:32.009
He's had lots
of offers.

26:32.050 --> 26:33.756
Even Maddie Hayward,
isn't that right?

26:33.790 --> 26:34.950
Yeah, she's great.

26:34.990 --> 26:36.116
A little green, maybe.

26:36.160 --> 26:37.718
So, you think you two
can work together?

26:37.760 --> 26:41.252
I heard you like
to work alone, Jordan.

26:41.300 --> 26:42.892
I do.

26:42.930 --> 26:45.364
But I also like to learn
from my elders.

26:47.370 --> 26:48.769
I just want
to get an idea

26:48.800 --> 26:50.028
how you might handle
certain situations, okay?

26:50.070 --> 26:51.105
Okay.

26:51.140 --> 26:54.303
Would you ever go into a store
and take something

26:54.340 --> 26:55.375
without paying
for it?

26:55.410 --> 26:56.570
KALEY:
No.

26:56.610 --> 26:59.408
MARTHA: If you got lost in
an airport, what would you do?

26:59.450 --> 27:01.918
Find a policeman
and ask him to help.

27:01.950 --> 27:04.987
Were you ever allowed to stay
home alone without a babysitter?

27:05.020 --> 27:06.942
Sometimes.

27:06.990 --> 27:08.309
Well, I used to.

27:08.360 --> 27:10.726
Not now,
because of what happened to me.

27:10.760 --> 27:12.022
Thank you, Kaley.

27:12.060 --> 27:13.254
That's all.

27:13.290 --> 27:15.758
Your client is mature enough
to understand right and wrong.

27:15.800 --> 27:17.290
Attractive nuisance
does not apply here.

27:17.330 --> 27:18.763
That's not for you
to decide.

27:18.800 --> 27:20.324
That's right.
It's for a jury.

27:20.370 --> 27:21.860
Which means court.

27:21.900 --> 27:23.390
Which means we're not
negotiating a settlement.

27:26.110 --> 27:27.907
Damn it.

27:27.940 --> 27:29.237
Still in a holding pattern.

27:29.280 --> 27:31.009
He's supposed to be here
in an hour,

27:31.050 --> 27:32.369
but I'm not holding my breath.

27:32.410 --> 27:34.014
We really need Ingersol.

27:34.050 --> 27:35.415
The case is
going down the drain.

27:35.450 --> 27:37.008
I think it's about this merger

27:37.050 --> 27:38.312
with Corsica Pacific.
What do you mean?

27:38.350 --> 27:41.251
Alicia, they're stalling

27:41.290 --> 27:43.679
because they don't want
a $13 million settlement

27:43.730 --> 27:45.379
to mess up
this merger.
Well, we can't wait.

27:45.430 --> 27:47.853
Alicia, is there any way you can
get proof they're stalling?

27:53.330 --> 27:55.036
Bad news, unfortunately.

27:55.070 --> 27:56.389
Really? What a surprise.

27:56.440 --> 27:58.237
Yeah, it'll have to be pushed
till this afternoon.

27:58.270 --> 27:59.362
Something came up
at the last minute.

27:59.410 --> 28:04.746
I say, it's pushed
till this afternoon.

28:04.780 --> 28:08.944
I thought we would use this time
to depose someone else.

28:08.980 --> 28:10.379
What, for practice?
Rita!

28:10.420 --> 28:12.183
What's going on here, Alicia?

28:12.220 --> 28:14.780
Please have a seat,
Ms. Neves.

28:14.820 --> 28:18.449
Would you state your name and
your occupation for the record?

28:18.490 --> 28:19.650
Rita Neves.

28:19.690 --> 28:23.251
I am a housekeeper here at
the Janesville Mountain Retreat.

28:23.300 --> 28:24.426
What, are we playing games here?

28:24.470 --> 28:26.290
And this morning,
were you near enough

28:26.330 --> 28:28.867
to Mr. Canning to overhear
his telephone conversation?

28:28.900 --> 28:30.333
_ RITA: Yes. I was
in his room cleaning

28:30.370 --> 28:32.930
while he was talking
on the phone.

28:32.970 --> 28:34.176
Objection. That's hearsay.

28:34.210 --> 28:35.279
Can you describe what you heard?

28:35.310 --> 28:37.778
He say, "No, don't come now.

28:37.810 --> 28:39.346
I call when Florrick steps out."

28:39.380 --> 28:40.347
Objection.

28:40.380 --> 28:42.439
That had nothing to do
with Wilkes Ingersol.

28:42.480 --> 28:44.448
Is that statement
for the record?

28:44.490 --> 28:46.310
This conversation is
totally taken out of context.

28:46.350 --> 28:48.386
It had nothing to do
with Wilkes Ingersol.

28:48.420 --> 28:52.823
It was to my...
partners in Chicago.

28:52.860 --> 28:54.327
Ed, you can come in now!

28:54.360 --> 28:55.258
What now, Mrs. Florrick?

28:55.300 --> 28:57.029
You got some farmers
you want to depose?

28:57.060 --> 28:59.062
Can you state your name
and occupation?

28:59.100 --> 29:01.239
Ed Jeffries.
I work at the front desk.

29:01.270 --> 29:03.761
And, um, can you tell me
how many calls were made

29:03.810 --> 29:05.038
from Mr. Canning's hotel room?

29:05.070 --> 29:06.059
Objection.

29:06.110 --> 29:07.065
Your objection has been

29:07.110 --> 29:08.179
preserved for the record.

29:08.210 --> 29:09.404
Please tell me
how many calls

29:09.440 --> 29:12.409
were placed from
Mr. Canning's room?

29:12.450 --> 29:14.270
Four.
That is private information.

29:14.320 --> 29:16.311
And were all those calls
placed to the same number?

29:16.350 --> 29:18.386
Three to the Ingersol Ranch,
one to another local number.

29:18.420 --> 29:20.308
So no calls were placed

29:20.350 --> 29:22.113
to Mr. Canning's partners
in Chicago?

29:22.160 --> 29:24.355
Well, there were no calls
to Chicago.

29:24.390 --> 29:26.221
Thank you, Ed.

29:34.940 --> 29:37.829
Oh.

29:37.870 --> 29:41.237
Don't you want to stay
for my call to the judge?

29:41.280 --> 29:44.272
Or do you want to be held
in contempt in absentia?

29:45.580 --> 29:47.775
(dialing)

29:50.150 --> 29:52.311
JUDGE:
Given this evidence,
Mr. Canning,

29:52.350 --> 29:53.886
I rule for the plaintiff.

29:53.920 --> 29:56.081
Present the witness
or be held in contempt.

29:56.120 --> 29:57.929
When is the earliest
he can be deposed?

29:57.960 --> 29:59.154
Tomorrow morning at 10:00.

29:59.190 --> 30:01.420
Your Honor, Mr. Canning has been
saying that for two days now.

30:01.460 --> 30:03.599
Mr. Ingersol is dealing
with an ongoing emergency.

30:03.630 --> 30:05.495
Mr. Canning,
have your client there

30:05.530 --> 30:07.521
at 10:00 a.m.
or be held in contempt.

30:07.570 --> 30:08.969
Do you understand?

30:09.000 --> 30:10.137
I do.

30:10.170 --> 30:12.434
(line clicks)

30:12.470 --> 30:14.472
I'll see you
at 10:00.

30:19.610 --> 30:21.578
I don't need a lawyer.

30:21.620 --> 30:24.942
Yes, but you never know
about the future, Mr. Ellstrom.

30:24.990 --> 30:26.218
Tobin.

30:26.250 --> 30:28.252
I'm not in politics
anymore, Ms. Lockhart.

30:28.290 --> 30:30.451
The Department of Justice
is making moves

30:30.490 --> 30:33.027
against past and current
campaign managers,

30:33.060 --> 30:36.120
so I think that you should
review your past campaigns.

30:36.160 --> 30:37.457
"Making moves"?

30:37.500 --> 30:39.024
On what issue?

30:39.070 --> 30:40.389
Discounts for donations.

30:40.430 --> 30:43.297
Campaign managers offering
discounted legal services

30:43.340 --> 30:45.535
in exchange
for campaign contributions.

30:45.570 --> 30:47.936
That's just Chicago politics.

30:47.980 --> 30:50.369
And since you were a lawyer
prior to your work

30:50.410 --> 30:53.277
as Wendy Scott-Carr's
campaign strategist,

30:53.310 --> 30:55.073
I thought there might be
some issue there.

30:55.120 --> 30:56.348
This is about
Wendy Scott-Carr?

30:56.380 --> 30:58.439
No.

30:58.490 --> 31:00.344
It's about
all your campaign work.

31:00.390 --> 31:02.654
But Wendy Scott-Carr
especially?

31:02.690 --> 31:04.351
Okay.

31:04.390 --> 31:06.051
I'll think about it.

31:06.090 --> 31:07.899
Certainly. Here's my card.

31:07.930 --> 31:09.921
Don't forget.

31:15.070 --> 31:16.367
(cell phone ringtone playing)

31:16.400 --> 31:18.038
Hello, Tobin.

31:18.070 --> 31:19.367
How nice to hear from you.

31:19.410 --> 31:22.004
TOBIN: Do you know a lavwer
named Diane Lockhart?

31:22.040 --> 31:23.439
Yes, I do. Why?

31:23.480 --> 31:26.301
She just approached me
about my past work with you.

31:26.350 --> 31:28.375
She did?

31:28.420 --> 31:30.172
Yeah, she said the Department
of Justice is investigating

31:30.220 --> 31:31.983
discounts for donations,
and that I might be implicated.

31:32.020 --> 31:33.988
(sighs)

31:34.020 --> 31:35.988
She wanted you to call me.

31:36.020 --> 31:36.987
What?

31:37.020 --> 31:38.521
She wanted you to call me

31:38.560 --> 31:40.528
so I would know
that if I pursue them

31:40.560 --> 31:43.552
on discounts for donations,
they'll pull you in.

31:43.600 --> 31:45.067
No, she just wanted me
to hire her.

31:45.100 --> 31:45.919
No, Tobin, she didn't.

31:45.970 --> 31:48.530
This was a warning shot
across my bow.

31:48.570 --> 31:50.595
So what are you gonna do?

31:50.640 --> 31:52.562
We ran a clean campaign, Tobin,
didn't we?

31:52.610 --> 31:55.670
Well, yes, but nothing's 100%.

31:55.710 --> 31:57.029
No, we ran

31:57.080 --> 31:59.640
a clean campaign.

31:59.680 --> 32:01.978
Just don't talk to her again.

32:04.650 --> 32:06.641
(knocking)

32:21.740 --> 32:24.163
Kalinda.

32:24.210 --> 32:25.507
And clothes.

32:25.540 --> 32:27.303
And incidentals.

32:27.340 --> 32:29.376
Ah.

32:34.780 --> 32:36.975
(sighs):
God, it's quiet.

32:39.120 --> 32:40.678
Yeah.

32:40.720 --> 32:42.415
You've had two days of this?

32:42.460 --> 32:44.428
And two nights.

32:44.460 --> 32:45.722
It's not that bad, actually.

32:45.760 --> 32:47.387
(sighs)

32:47.430 --> 32:48.454
Really?

32:48.500 --> 32:49.728
I'd kill someone.

32:52.730 --> 32:55.267
You know what I miss
about my old life?

32:55.300 --> 32:57.768
Before the glamour of the law?

32:57.800 --> 32:59.734
What?

32:59.770 --> 33:01.977
The quiet.

33:03.040 --> 33:05.144
At home, in the afternoons,

33:05.180 --> 33:08.274
I would drink every day at 3:00.

33:08.320 --> 33:11.289
A glass of red wine.

33:11.320 --> 33:14.016
Waiting for the kids
to come home.

33:16.220 --> 33:20.179
I miss the silence
in the house at 3:00.

33:20.230 --> 33:22.221
Just...

33:23.730 --> 33:25.721
...nothing going on.

33:28.440 --> 33:30.431
I miss this.

33:35.480 --> 33:37.436
Yeah.

33:37.480 --> 33:39.744
(chuckles softly)

33:39.780 --> 33:41.645
I'm sorry.

33:45.850 --> 33:48.114
I know.

33:50.720 --> 33:52.722
(chuckles softly)

33:54.800 --> 33:56.620
You know, I don't think

33:56.660 --> 33:59.060
Ingersol's gonna show up
tomorrow at 10:00.

33:59.100 --> 34:00.624
I know.

34:00.670 --> 34:02.638
Cary thinks that
they're trying to avoid

34:02.670 --> 34:04.661
a road bump
in their merger.

34:05.770 --> 34:09.069
Do you have that other number
Canning was calling?

34:09.110 --> 34:13.069
There were three to the ranch
and one to a local number.

34:13.110 --> 34:14.418
Yeah.

34:14.450 --> 34:15.610
What's your thinking?

34:16.650 --> 34:18.345
(sighs):
I don't know.

34:18.390 --> 34:20.381
Maybe there's a real emergency.

34:22.860 --> 34:26.421
Cary Agos. A fourth-year
associate at Lockhart/Gardner.

34:26.460 --> 34:30.499
DIANE:
And were you asked by Mr. Hayden
for your assistance

34:30.530 --> 34:32.691
over the last three months?
Yes.

34:32.730 --> 34:35.563
And for how many hours a week
were you asked to help him?

34:35.600 --> 34:36.737
Roughly...

34:36.770 --> 34:37.839
ten hours a week.

34:37.870 --> 34:39.735
And this was done
on your time?

34:39.770 --> 34:41.533
CARY:
As a fourth-year
associate,

34:41.580 --> 34:43.832
very few hours in a day
actually constitute my time.

34:43.880 --> 34:44.869
But you managed?

34:44.910 --> 34:47.105
Yes. Yes, I did manage.

34:47.150 --> 34:49.778
DIANE:
And what did Mr. Hayden
ask of you?

34:50.820 --> 34:53.448
He asked me
to be his tutor.

34:53.490 --> 34:54.787
DIANE:
His tutor?

34:54.820 --> 34:56.458
Yes.

34:56.490 --> 34:59.527
He asked me to help him study
for the upcoming bar exam.

34:59.560 --> 35:01.755
DIANE:
And what prompted
that arrangement?

35:01.800 --> 35:04.769
Mr. Hayden had attended
law school years earlier,

35:04.800 --> 35:07.462
but never attempted
to pass the bar.

35:07.500 --> 35:11.209
Now working at Lockhart/Gardner
had reinvigorated him.

35:11.240 --> 35:14.209
DIANE:
And did you feel you had
any choice in the matter

35:14.240 --> 35:15.468
but to help him?

35:17.910 --> 35:19.878
No.

35:19.910 --> 35:22.219
Thank you, Mr. Agos.

35:23.250 --> 35:25.480
Anything, Mr. Hayden?

35:28.490 --> 35:30.754
Uh, yes.

35:30.790 --> 35:34.419
Uh, you stated
that fourth-year associates

35:34.460 --> 35:36.758
rarely have time of their own.

35:36.800 --> 35:37.824
Yes.

35:37.860 --> 35:40.590
But you found the time
to help me?

35:42.600 --> 35:45.603
I didn't feel
as if I had a choice.

35:45.640 --> 35:48.438
You held sway
over the entire firm.

35:50.240 --> 35:53.846
Isn't it true that I offered
to pay you for your a55istance?

35:53.880 --> 35:55.518
Yes, you did.

35:55.550 --> 35:57.848
And did you
refuse my offer?
Yes.

35:57.880 --> 36:00.314
Did I ever state or imply
that you would be afforded

36:00.350 --> 36:01.817
preferential treatment
for your help?

36:01.860 --> 36:04.658
No, you did not.
Did I ever state or imply

36:04.690 --> 36:08.194
that you would be penalized
if you refused to help me?

36:09.230 --> 36:12.199
No, you did not.

36:12.230 --> 36:14.892
Your Honor...
"Ma'am."

36:14.940 --> 36:17.534
Ma'am.

36:17.570 --> 36:19.834
Lockhart/Gardner...

36:19.870 --> 36:21.838
has no shame

36:21.880 --> 36:25.304
in trying to besmirch my name
for their own personal gain.

36:25.350 --> 36:26.647
It goes to their...

36:26.680 --> 36:30.673
illogical passion for
winning at all costs.

36:32.950 --> 36:36.556
Once again, I ask that
Diane Lockhart and Will Gardner

36:36.590 --> 36:39.582
be removed from their managerial
positions at the firm.

36:40.960 --> 36:43.929
I'll take your words
under advisement, Mr. Hayden.

37:00.910 --> 37:02.468
Ingersol's not dodging
the depositions

37:02.520 --> 37:03.646
because of the merger.

37:03.680 --> 37:04.908
WILL:
Why then?

37:04.950 --> 37:08.613
He's been seeking treatment at
an experimental cancer center.

37:09.660 --> 37:11.525
He's... Since when?

37:11.560 --> 37:13.528
A few months ago.
The number Canning

37:13.560 --> 37:16.654
dialed from here was a center
run by Vivek Assadullah,

37:16.700 --> 37:18.520
a cancer specialist.

37:18.570 --> 37:20.959
Ingersol's battling
non-Hodgkin lymphoma.

37:21.000 --> 37:22.763
That's not public knowledge.

37:22.800 --> 37:23.892
No, it's not.

37:23.940 --> 37:25.464
Thanks, Kalinda.
Is Alicia there?

37:25.510 --> 37:27.501
Sure. Alicia.

37:29.540 --> 37:31.007
Yeah?

37:31.040 --> 37:32.974
Use it. They don't want it
to come out before the merger.

37:33.010 --> 37:34.671
I know. I'm on it.

37:34.720 --> 37:36.312
(indistinct chattering)

37:36.350 --> 37:38.989
What the hell?

37:39.020 --> 37:41.853
Oh, no. Ms. Scott-Carr,
do you have an appointment?

37:41.890 --> 37:44.654
No. We're here to confiscate
Eli Gold's files.

37:44.690 --> 37:46.749
He operated
his crisis management ﬁrm

37:46.790 --> 37:49.054
out of these offices,
which makes Lockhart/Gardner

37:49.100 --> 37:50.727
open to investigation as well.

37:50.760 --> 37:51.988
That is bizarrely tenuous.

37:52.030 --> 37:55.329
And yet, supported by the judge.

37:55.970 --> 37:57.369
Thank you...

37:57.400 --> 37:59.561
for the warning shot.

37:59.610 --> 38:01.578
It gave me time
to acquire the warrant.

38:01.610 --> 38:03.908
This investigation
is so hypocritical.

38:03.940 --> 38:06.647
Okay, the files in here first.

38:16.460 --> 38:18.451
(clock ticking)

38:19.090 --> 38:20.626
Don't worry.
He's coming.

38:20.660 --> 38:22.457
He's just... a
few minutes late.

38:26.630 --> 38:28.632
(car approaching)

38:31.440 --> 38:33.431
O ye of little faith.

38:34.480 --> 38:36.573
(car doors shut)

38:36.610 --> 38:37.702
ALICIA:
Good afternoon,
Mr. Ingersol,

38:37.740 --> 38:39.002
and welcome back.
Thank you.

38:39.050 --> 38:41.302
How are you feeling today?

38:42.150 --> 38:43.777
Good. Why?

38:43.820 --> 38:45.742
Just a pleasantry.

38:46.790 --> 38:48.781
Well... thank you.

38:48.820 --> 38:50.788
I'm good.
(chuckles)

38:50.820 --> 38:53.687
Good. Why don't we pick up
where we left off.

38:53.730 --> 38:55.425
Did you see this letter

38:55.460 --> 38:57.655
that was written by the
residents of the community,

38:57.700 --> 38:59.964
complaining about the state
of the five foreclosed homes

39:00.000 --> 39:01.126
and their swimming pools?

39:01.170 --> 39:02.694
I, uh, did not.

39:02.740 --> 39:03.934
You see it's addressed to you?

39:03.970 --> 39:05.107
I do.

39:05.140 --> 39:07.062
IfI read every letter
addressed to me,

39:07.110 --> 39:09.578
I wouldn't have time
to... shave or sleep.

39:09.610 --> 39:11.840
(chuckling)

39:13.080 --> 39:14.718
So that answers that, Alicia.

39:14.750 --> 39:16.638
Any other questions?

39:16.680 --> 39:18.648
Mr. Ingersol, are you aware

39:18.690 --> 39:21.113
that it is an SEC violation
to withhold an illness

39:21.150 --> 39:22.811
from shareholders?

39:22.860 --> 39:24.725
Objection. Relevance.

39:24.760 --> 39:26.022
Your objection
has been noted.

39:26.060 --> 39:28.722
Are you aware
that it is an SEC violation?

39:30.630 --> 39:33.827
Yes, but I'm not sure what this
has to do with your lawsuit.

39:33.870 --> 39:34.768
It has to do

39:34.800 --> 39:37.769
with your intent to delay,
Mr. Ingersol.

39:37.800 --> 39:40.007
Atlantic Commerce is
a publicly held company.

39:40.040 --> 39:42.873
The shareholders have a right
to know if the leader

39:42.910 --> 39:45.970
is facing
a critical illness.

39:46.010 --> 39:48.444
And according to his profile,

39:48.480 --> 39:50.778
Dr. Vivek Assadullah
is a specialist

39:50.820 --> 39:52.617
who conducts
experimental treatments

39:52.650 --> 39:54.379
for non-Hodgkin lymphoma.
CANNING:
Objection.

39:55.220 --> 39:57.188
This is beneath you, Alicia.
No,

39:57.220 --> 39:58.824
unfortunately, it's not.

40:03.830 --> 40:07.823
The emergency you were dealing
with, Mr. Ingersol, was...

40:09.100 --> 40:10.761
Uh, Ms. Court Reporter,

40:10.800 --> 40:12.802
do you mind stepping out
for a moment, please?

40:12.840 --> 40:14.728
My name is Mika.

40:14.780 --> 40:17.078
So sorry. Mika. Of course.

40:20.780 --> 40:23.544
(door opens)
You were being treated
for non-Hodgkin lymphoma,

40:23.580 --> 40:25.548
and you didn't want
this knowledge made public

40:25.590 --> 40:27.615
before your merger
with Corsica Pacific.

40:29.890 --> 40:33.781
This does not have to go
on the record, Mr. Ingersol.

40:33.830 --> 40:35.889
We have been trying
for weeks now

40:35.930 --> 40:37.727
to negotiate with Mr. Canning.

40:37.760 --> 40:41.491
And if you approve
this settlement of $15 million,

40:41.540 --> 40:43.929
the questioning
can end right here.

40:50.780 --> 40:52.042
(door opens)

40:52.080 --> 40:53.775
DIANE:
Uh,

40:53.810 --> 40:54.913
one second, Eli.

40:54.950 --> 40:55.939
(quietly):
Alicia?

40:55.980 --> 40:57.675
Yes. $12 million.

40:57.720 --> 40:58.846
$3 million to us.

40:58.890 --> 41:00.517
Uh, good.

41:00.550 --> 41:02.017
I'll be right
there. Yeah.

41:02.060 --> 41:04.824
As I was saying, Eli,
unfortunately,

41:04.860 --> 41:07.829
this changes everything.
Wendy's doing this
so you can't be my lawyer.

41:07.860 --> 41:10.499
I know. But now
that we're part of this...

41:10.530 --> 41:12.088
probe into your practices,

41:12.130 --> 41:13.893
we are precluded
from representing you.

41:13.930 --> 41:15.761
We have a list
of potential attorneys.

41:15.800 --> 41:16.732
I've called the top three.

41:16.770 --> 41:19.830
All are ready for your call.
And so it goes,

41:19.870 --> 41:23.078
the endless cycle
of Chicago investigations.

41:23.110 --> 41:26.238
JORDAN:
Hey, guys. Do you know when
the old man is coming back?

41:26.280 --> 41:28.714
Eli. There you are.

41:28.750 --> 41:30.047
Let's talk
about debate prep.

41:30.080 --> 41:31.889
Let's.
Maddie Hayward is

41:31.920 --> 41:32.909
putting all her time into prep.

41:32.950 --> 41:34.611
That's when she really wants
to make her mark.

41:34.660 --> 41:35.911
And I looked at
the schedule, and you...

41:35.960 --> 41:37.916
you barely have
Peter down.

41:37.960 --> 41:39.086
WILL:
We received

41:39.130 --> 41:41.553
a settlement offer today
for $12 million.

41:41.600 --> 41:43.090
DIANE:
And just today,
Encinal Equity

41:43.130 --> 41:45.860
completed their purchase
of Lockhart/Gardner debt.

41:45.900 --> 41:48.892
They are invested
in our financial health,

41:48.940 --> 41:50.134
and we intend to honor
that commitment.

41:50.170 --> 41:51.432
Mr. Hayden,

41:51.470 --> 41:56.078
I understand your disappointment
in losing a merger opportunity,

41:56.110 --> 41:59.841
but I do believe
this purchase of debt suggests

41:59.880 --> 42:02.815
the financial community
has faith in management.

42:02.850 --> 42:04.886
Therefore, I
have determined

42:04.920 --> 42:07.309
Ms. Lockhart and Mr. Gardner not

42:07.350 --> 42:08.954
be removed
as managing partners

42:08.990 --> 42:11.652
and that they continue

42:11.690 --> 42:12.987
to work, with
your guidance,

42:13.030 --> 42:15.828
toward financial health.
After the deadline,

42:15.860 --> 42:17.555
five weeks from now,

42:17.600 --> 42:20.319
Mr. Hayden, then you might find
a merger partner.

42:20.370 --> 42:22.998
That's my ruling.

42:25.870 --> 42:28.304
(door shuts)
Escaped the executioner.

42:28.340 --> 42:29.898
WILL:
For now.

42:29.940 --> 42:31.942
We can never meet
a five-week deadline.

42:31.980 --> 42:33.242
I know.

42:33.280 --> 42:35.578
We talk to the new creditor.

42:35.620 --> 42:37.076
Get an extension?

42:37.120 --> 42:38.439
(thunder rumbles)

42:42.320 --> 42:43.856
SIMONE:
Alicia.

42:43.890 --> 42:46.222
I'm so sorry we didn't get
to have that breakfast.

42:46.260 --> 42:47.659
Oh, me, too.

42:47.690 --> 42:48.896
You heading out?

42:48.930 --> 42:50.989
Yeah, Louis has
business, so...

42:51.030 --> 42:52.190
no rest.

42:52.230 --> 42:53.720
Be seeing you soon.

42:53.770 --> 42:55.169
And why's that?

42:55.200 --> 42:57.031
Oh, you didn't hear?

42:58.100 --> 43:00.967
I purchased
the Lockhart/Gardner debt.

43:01.010 --> 43:03.137
I'm your new creditor.

43:04.180 --> 43:05.807
You two will be working
together?

43:05.850 --> 43:06.908
That's fantastic.

